WEBVTT

00:02:09.662 --> 00:02:11.839
[Roommate Agreement]

00:02:21.941 --> 00:02:23.541
I'll keep using that room, then.

00:02:23.541 --> 00:02:25.334
It's already completely cleaned out.

00:02:25.334 --> 00:02:28.050
Perfect for staying a month and moving out.

00:02:28.050 --> 00:02:30.158
That room is...

00:02:30.158 --> 00:02:32.410
Why?

00:02:32.410 --> 00:02:36.122
You want me to take the master? I don't mind.

00:02:36.122 --> 00:02:37.692
Go ahead.

00:02:37.692 --> 00:02:40.182
But don't touch anything in there.

00:02:40.182 --> 00:02:42.351
That's my one request.

00:02:42.351 --> 00:02:45.396
From now on, that room is off-limits.

00:02:45.396 --> 00:02:47.356
My stuff, my furniture, and so on.

00:02:47.356 --> 00:02:48.482
Not shared. Okay?

00:02:48.482 --> 00:02:50.568
If you need to come in...

00:02:50.568 --> 00:02:52.732
Don't forget.

00:02:56.871 --> 00:02:58.399
[In-law]

00:03:01.777 --> 00:03:03.298
[Temporary housing]
[Temporary helper]

00:03:10.573 --> 00:03:13.305
I haven't seen glow-in-the-dark stars
in forever.

00:03:13.305 --> 00:03:16.183
My babies, I kept you safe.

00:03:16.183 --> 00:03:17.943
Hang in there for one month.

00:03:17.943 --> 00:03:19.263
I'll let you out soon.

00:03:19.263 --> 00:03:23.288
Just until I settle into my new job.

00:03:23.288 --> 00:03:25.534
That's okay, right?

00:03:33.194 --> 00:03:34.527
It's just one month, right?

00:03:34.527 --> 00:03:37.406
Seriously. One month. Exactly one month.

00:03:37.406 --> 00:03:38.741
No staying longer after that.

00:03:38.741 --> 00:03:40.076
My thoughts exactly.

00:03:40.076 --> 00:03:42.915
A month from now,
it won't matter how much you beg.

00:03:42.915 --> 00:03:44.747
Wait, aren't you working?

00:03:44.747 --> 00:03:48.252
When I go to work,
who's taking care of Woo Joo?

00:03:55.925 --> 00:03:57.760
[Episode 3]
Weren't you single?

00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:58.985
He's not on my family register,

00:03:58.985 --> 00:04:00.387
but that kid is mine.

00:04:00.387 --> 00:04:01.447
For one month.

00:04:01.447 --> 00:04:02.500
Danny...

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:04.456
Annual, monthly, Fridays off, everything.

00:04:04.456 --> 00:04:06.914
I want to use all my leave.

00:04:06.914 --> 00:04:07.940
Just one month.

00:04:07.940 --> 00:04:10.766
- Please approve it.
- A month?

00:04:11.398 --> 00:04:12.817
Look around this place.

00:04:12.817 --> 00:04:14.693
Our only photographer ran off

00:04:14.693 --> 00:04:17.613
said he'd shoot models instead of motels.

00:04:17.613 --> 00:04:19.434
It's a total crisis.

00:04:19.434 --> 00:04:21.492
Last year, when you took
a full year off for parental leave,

00:04:21.492 --> 00:04:22.952
all the delayed deadlines,

00:04:22.952 --> 00:04:24.045
all those complaints,

00:04:24.045 --> 00:04:26.288
I was the one who dealt with them.

00:04:26.288 --> 00:04:28.181
When I joined this company three years ago,

00:04:28.181 --> 00:04:30.126
you know what I gave up to be here.

00:04:30.126 --> 00:04:32.336
Yeah. I know.

00:04:32.336 --> 00:04:34.922
[Parental Leave Application]
Because of your house, that photo...

00:04:34.922 --> 00:04:36.966
Oh, the photo?

00:04:36.966 --> 00:04:39.176
You used to do photography.

00:04:39.176 --> 00:04:40.369
That was a long time ago.

00:04:40.369 --> 00:04:42.780
It still happened.

00:04:42.780 --> 00:04:44.742
Danny.

00:04:44.742 --> 00:04:47.468
You said you wanted a month off, right?

00:05:25.264 --> 00:05:27.850
I know you hate even looking at a camera.

00:05:27.850 --> 00:05:29.810
Please. Just help me once.

00:05:29.810 --> 00:05:30.978
If we wrap this up,

00:05:30.978 --> 00:05:34.447
I'll approve your one-month parental leave.

00:05:59.965 --> 00:06:02.684
What is this motel?

00:06:09.475 --> 00:06:11.398
This isn't it either.

00:06:11.398 --> 00:06:14.104
Find another location.

00:06:24.934 --> 00:06:26.299
[Top Photographer Amy Choo
Cancels Again on Shoot Day]

00:06:26.299 --> 00:06:28.244
The photo selection's not good.

00:06:28.244 --> 00:06:31.830
If I'd shot it,
I'd have given it more tonal contrast.

00:06:31.830 --> 00:06:33.624
Is this really the time to say that?

00:06:33.624 --> 00:06:35.542
How are we supposed to fix this?

00:06:35.542 --> 00:06:37.336
Why is that on me?

00:06:37.336 --> 00:06:38.963
That's your job.

00:06:38.963 --> 00:06:40.631
I reschedule the shoots,

00:06:40.631 --> 00:06:43.219
I book the locations, I pick up the equipment.

00:06:43.219 --> 00:06:46.178
Do you think I have a hundred bodies?

00:06:46.178 --> 00:06:49.056
Get me an assistant. Seriously.

00:06:49.056 --> 00:06:50.496
Do I really need one?

00:06:50.496 --> 00:06:52.643
When you're right here?

00:06:52.643 --> 00:06:54.019
This place is not good.

00:06:54.019 --> 00:06:55.854
I'd sleep too well here.

00:06:55.854 --> 00:06:57.439
What's wrong with that?

00:06:57.439 --> 00:07:00.198
Does someone at rock bottom sleep this well?

00:07:00.198 --> 00:07:03.028
We need something trashier, grimmer,

00:07:03.028 --> 00:07:04.488
more sleazy.

00:07:04.488 --> 00:07:05.739
You get what I mean?

00:07:05.739 --> 00:07:07.199
No. I really don't.

00:07:07.199 --> 00:07:08.742
Then where is that, exactly?

00:07:08.742 --> 00:07:12.354
That's why you need to look harder.

00:07:12.354 --> 00:07:14.130
On your own.

00:07:14.130 --> 00:07:16.875
You said the Palace Motel was awful
because of the gold-trim mirrors,

00:07:16.875 --> 00:07:20.796
and the Chocolate Motel was bad
because of the flashing LED headboard.

00:07:20.796 --> 00:07:24.649
Because of you,
I've checked out over 500 motels nationwide.

00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:27.970
Yeah.

00:07:27.970 --> 00:07:30.681
Something trashier, grimmer,

00:07:30.681 --> 00:07:32.528
more sleazy.

00:07:32.528 --> 00:07:33.559
What?

00:07:33.559 --> 00:07:36.563
You're saying just shoot anywhere?

00:07:36.563 --> 00:07:39.481
she got that far
because she takes her work seriously.

00:07:39.481 --> 00:07:40.733
That's Amy Choo.

00:07:40.733 --> 00:07:42.109
Openly more sultry...

00:07:42.109 --> 00:07:43.610
grimmer,

00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:44.945
grimmer,

00:07:44.945 --> 00:07:46.447
more sleazy.

00:07:46.447 --> 00:07:47.614
more sleazy.

00:07:47.614 --> 00:07:50.547
Yeah. Exactly like that.

00:07:53.662 --> 00:07:55.561
You could lean into red lighting like this,

00:07:55.561 --> 00:07:58.122
make it way more intimate.

00:07:59.335 --> 00:08:00.961
Or strip all this out

00:08:00.961 --> 00:08:02.463
and go raw and real.

00:08:02.463 --> 00:08:04.606
Oh, okay.

00:08:08.719 --> 00:08:11.972
Are you a photographer?

00:08:11.972 --> 00:08:14.739
I'm not a weirdo.

00:08:17.728 --> 00:08:20.521
I'm working with Amy Choo.

00:08:23.609 --> 00:08:25.402
Parenting tips for a 20-month-old.

00:08:25.402 --> 00:08:27.249
Here are a few things to keep in mind.

00:08:27.249 --> 00:08:30.282
Tantrums are a form of communication.

00:08:30.282 --> 00:08:31.473
Talk to them a lot.

00:08:31.473 --> 00:08:33.202
A lot...

00:08:33.202 --> 00:08:35.479
[Sleep routine matters!]
Let's talk a lot.

00:08:42.628 --> 00:08:44.004
Woo Joo.

00:08:44.004 --> 00:08:46.902
Eat well while I'm gone,

00:08:46.902 --> 00:08:48.659
and have fun playing.

00:08:48.659 --> 00:08:50.740
Okay?

00:09:17.079 --> 00:09:18.705
Wow.

00:09:18.705 --> 00:09:21.500
Can you sell this to me?

00:09:21.500 --> 00:09:23.544
No, wait...

00:09:23.544 --> 00:09:27.092
Could I borrow you for just one day?

00:09:27.092 --> 00:09:28.952
I've got a really great opportunity

00:09:28.952 --> 00:09:31.677
to work under Amy Choo.

00:09:31.677 --> 00:09:34.518
I'll pay you a million won for the day.

00:09:35.848 --> 00:09:38.228
Not interested.

00:09:46.017 --> 00:09:47.601
Please stop knocking.

00:09:47.601 --> 00:09:48.926
You're going to break the door.

00:09:48.926 --> 00:09:52.299
You said we should communicate by knocking.

00:10:00.789 --> 00:10:02.660
Don't take this the wrong way.

00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:05.229
I've just been doing this for a while.

00:10:06.503 --> 00:10:08.756
You want me to check all of this every day?

00:10:08.756 --> 00:10:11.169
I want to raise Woo Joo

00:10:11.169 --> 00:10:13.886
at a normal pace.

00:10:13.886 --> 00:10:15.412
I'd like you to organize it by time

00:10:15.412 --> 00:10:17.014
and share it with me.

00:10:17.014 --> 00:10:19.558
You want real-time updates too?

00:10:19.558 --> 00:10:22.355
Given your track record, yes.

00:10:22.355 --> 00:10:25.582
You fed him chocolate and ketchup. Right?

00:10:26.899 --> 00:10:29.620
That was early education.

00:10:29.620 --> 00:10:31.191
What if you break the nine-to-six rule?

00:10:31.191 --> 00:10:32.988
That won't happen.

00:10:32.988 --> 00:10:35.127
From now on,

00:10:35.127 --> 00:10:36.738
as co-parents,

00:10:36.738 --> 00:10:40.525
let's always keep in mind
that Woo Joo comes first.

00:10:44.223 --> 00:10:45.382
She's something else.

00:10:45.382 --> 00:10:47.671
I can hear you, in-law.

00:10:51.363 --> 00:10:52.716
So annoying.

00:10:52.716 --> 00:10:55.656
I can hear that too, in-law.

00:11:02.044 --> 00:11:03.813
You're eating so well.

00:11:04.853 --> 00:11:06.806
Here.

00:11:08.695 --> 00:11:11.028
Woo Joo, hold on.

00:11:14.363 --> 00:11:17.130
Here. I have to head out.

00:11:17.130 --> 00:11:18.575
It's not nine yet.

00:11:18.575 --> 00:11:20.917
Come on, nine to six is my schedule.

00:11:20.917 --> 00:11:23.119
You're supposed to work around mine.

00:11:23.119 --> 00:11:24.498
Eight to seven. Okay?

00:11:24.498 --> 00:11:25.707
Are you serious?

00:11:25.707 --> 00:11:27.971
You know overtime applies if it's like this.

00:11:27.971 --> 00:11:29.086
So...

00:11:29.086 --> 00:11:31.964
You should've read the contract
before signing it.

00:11:31.964 --> 00:11:34.526
If you don't like it, you can leave.

00:11:35.676 --> 00:11:37.219
Trust and faith...

00:11:37.219 --> 00:11:39.304
Let's build it. Together.

00:11:39.304 --> 00:11:40.556
In-law.

00:11:40.556 --> 00:11:44.884
Let's show it through our actions.
Like professionals.

00:11:44.884 --> 00:11:46.895
Woo Joo.

00:11:46.895 --> 00:11:48.230
I'm heading out.

00:11:48.230 --> 00:11:49.231
Bye-bye.

00:11:49.231 --> 00:11:50.315
See you later.

00:11:50.315 --> 00:11:52.188
Okay.

00:11:54.287 --> 00:11:57.131
Alright, here comes your food.

00:12:04.482 --> 00:12:05.629
Auntie?

00:12:05.629 --> 00:12:08.224
Your auntie went to work.

00:12:08.224 --> 00:12:10.204
Water.

00:12:13.791 --> 00:12:15.531
- More?
- Yeah.

00:12:15.531 --> 00:12:17.192
Excuse me.

00:12:17.192 --> 00:12:18.337
Sorry.

00:12:18.337 --> 00:12:20.558
Excuse me.

00:12:52.071 --> 00:12:57.009
[Welcome, New Hires
Who Will Shape the Future of BS FOOD]

00:12:57.785 --> 00:12:59.887
[Training materials
for new employees]

00:13:21.559 --> 00:13:23.479
[BS FOOD, Woo Hyun Jin]

00:13:40.175 --> 00:13:42.202
Why does she leave a perfectly good room

00:13:42.202 --> 00:13:44.677
and live in the living room?

00:13:50.880 --> 00:13:52.614
[Picture book: helps develop creativity]

00:13:52.614 --> 00:13:55.732
Creativity? Beats me.

00:13:55.732 --> 00:13:59.027
Thought we had Dr. Oh Eun Kyung here.

00:13:59.027 --> 00:14:03.782
My baby's already boosting creativity
through audiovisual learning.

00:14:03.782 --> 00:14:06.556
Oh, right. I should report this.

00:14:07.911 --> 00:14:09.955
To briefly explain what BS FOOD is,

00:14:09.955 --> 00:14:11.665
we're a company

00:14:11.665 --> 00:14:14.584
that cooks value beyond taste.

00:14:14.584 --> 00:14:15.667
So now...

00:14:15.667 --> 00:14:16.732
Just like auntie,

00:14:16.732 --> 00:14:19.367
baby's creativity and language skills
are growing!

00:14:19.367 --> 00:14:22.073
[Creativity up!]
You keep it up too.

00:14:23.927 --> 00:14:25.178
This is a BS product.

00:14:25.178 --> 00:14:26.680
Enjoy your meal.

00:14:26.680 --> 00:14:27.831
In a bit,

00:14:27.831 --> 00:14:29.937
it'll be time to fill out your evaluation form.

00:14:29.937 --> 00:14:33.723
Baby is eating independently.

00:14:36.648 --> 00:14:38.934
If you don't want it, don't eat it.

00:14:43.648 --> 00:14:46.867
She said not to feed him just chocolate...

00:14:49.620 --> 00:14:52.657
[Balanced Meal]

00:14:52.657 --> 00:14:54.374
- Is it good?
- Yeah.

00:14:54.374 --> 00:14:55.459
More?

00:14:55.459 --> 00:14:57.256
Yeah.

00:14:57.256 --> 00:14:59.056
[Evaluation Form]

00:15:00.969 --> 00:15:02.424
Visited a kids cafe.

00:15:02.424 --> 00:15:05.135
Working on gross motor skills.

00:15:05.822 --> 00:15:08.036
[Gross Motor Skills]

00:15:10.954 --> 00:15:12.058
You can use it.

00:15:12.058 --> 00:15:13.101
And everyone,

00:15:13.101 --> 00:15:15.247
you know we get a 50 percent discount, right?

00:15:15.247 --> 00:15:16.521
Starting to teach the baby

00:15:16.521 --> 00:15:18.190
what "no" means.

00:15:18.190 --> 00:15:20.471
No. Wait.

00:15:20.471 --> 00:15:22.658
[Building Patience]

00:15:24.808 --> 00:15:28.139
That wraps up today's new hire orientation.

00:15:28.139 --> 00:15:29.601
Thank you for your hard work.

00:15:29.601 --> 00:15:32.069
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:15:48.762 --> 00:15:50.263
Hey, baby.

00:15:50.263 --> 00:15:52.808
Stay right there for ten minutes.

00:15:52.808 --> 00:15:56.027
Save the squirming
for when your aunt gets back.

00:15:57.687 --> 00:16:00.166
This is nice.

00:16:02.982 --> 00:16:05.159
So... that means

00:16:05.159 --> 00:16:08.170
I have to do this for a whole month?

00:16:17.467 --> 00:16:19.560
That's cold.

00:16:26.258 --> 00:16:28.426
What are you doing right now?

00:16:28.426 --> 00:16:29.536
What do you mean?

00:16:29.536 --> 00:16:33.002
The boiler just cut out.
I got blasted with cold water.

00:16:38.603 --> 00:16:40.816
This must be it.

00:16:42.148 --> 00:16:44.328
Maybe this?

00:16:51.825 --> 00:16:54.369
You said you were into DIY.

00:16:54.369 --> 00:16:56.545
You don't know how to fix this?

00:16:58.623 --> 00:17:02.460
I'm more about aesthetics than actual systems.

00:17:02.460 --> 00:17:04.462
You're seriously no help.

00:17:04.462 --> 00:17:06.214
I've never lived in a dump like this.

00:17:06.214 --> 00:17:07.911
My place was brand new.

00:17:07.911 --> 00:17:09.744
Hot water all day.

00:17:09.744 --> 00:17:11.428
Whenever something like this happened,

00:17:11.428 --> 00:17:13.880
my sister always...

00:17:18.212 --> 00:17:19.244
[Gas Boiler]

00:17:19.244 --> 00:17:21.229
There's a separate service fee?

00:17:21.229 --> 00:17:22.439
No, no.

00:17:22.439 --> 00:17:24.874
Please don't book anything yet.

00:17:25.650 --> 00:17:26.735
Why?

00:17:26.735 --> 00:17:28.320
They said it's a million won.

00:17:28.320 --> 00:17:30.196
That's insane. Hang up.

00:17:30.196 --> 00:17:31.281
Yes.

00:17:31.281 --> 00:17:33.617
Thank you.

00:17:33.617 --> 00:17:36.052
A million won?

00:17:36.703 --> 00:17:39.164
We still have to bathe Woo Joo.

00:17:39.164 --> 00:17:41.833
Why did you shower first?

00:17:41.833 --> 00:17:45.653
What if the water went cold
while bathing the baby?

00:17:46.463 --> 00:17:47.631
Anyway...

00:17:47.631 --> 00:17:50.871
What are we going to do about him?

00:17:50.871 --> 00:17:52.511
That's...

00:17:52.511 --> 00:17:55.837
something you'll handle, in-law.

00:17:55.837 --> 00:17:57.940
You got this.

00:17:59.599 --> 00:18:02.278
Gosh, he's so strict.

00:18:05.748 --> 00:18:07.981
Where is it?

00:18:10.403 --> 00:18:12.197
I can't rest with all this noise.

00:18:12.197 --> 00:18:14.490
- What's going on?
- I'm looking for a washbasin.

00:18:14.490 --> 00:18:17.084
The tub feels too big.

00:18:19.871 --> 00:18:20.997
How about this?

00:18:20.997 --> 00:18:22.540
You trying to boil the baby?

00:18:22.540 --> 00:18:24.093
Just use the bathtub.

00:18:24.093 --> 00:18:26.588
Hold on, in-law.

00:18:26.588 --> 00:18:28.922
You can at least help hold him.

00:18:28.922 --> 00:18:31.275
If you have any decency at all.

00:18:43.770 --> 00:18:46.405
I'm on baby duty.

00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:52.570
Can't you see he's all pruney?

00:18:52.570 --> 00:18:53.666
All the grime's coming out.

00:18:53.666 --> 00:18:55.073
Then just scrub it off.

00:18:55.073 --> 00:18:57.409
Scrub yourself. You'll ruin the baby's skin.

00:18:57.409 --> 00:18:59.320
What?

00:19:02.288 --> 00:19:05.881
- My eyes...
- Hold him tighter.

00:19:06.584 --> 00:19:07.627
You doing this on purpose?

00:19:07.627 --> 00:19:08.860
How long are we bathing him?

00:19:08.860 --> 00:19:10.071
The water's getting cold.

00:19:10.071 --> 00:19:12.697
Let's hurry up and get out.

00:19:19.431 --> 00:19:21.783
Good job.

00:19:22.642 --> 00:19:24.227
You really did great.

00:19:24.227 --> 00:19:26.637
I'm so proud of you, Sun Tae Hyung.

00:19:27.938 --> 00:19:30.066
If you'd just held him properly,

00:19:30.066 --> 00:19:32.110
we'd have been done half an hour ago.

00:19:32.110 --> 00:19:34.150
I basically volunteered here.

00:19:34.150 --> 00:19:35.655
Look.

00:19:35.655 --> 00:19:37.824
Have you no shame?

00:19:37.824 --> 00:19:41.003
You're so cheap.

00:19:41.003 --> 00:19:42.935
What?

00:19:47.250 --> 00:19:49.010
No, Woo Joo!

00:19:49.010 --> 00:19:51.909
Stop!

00:20:10.885 --> 00:20:13.462
Between you and the baby,
who do you think looks dirtier?

00:20:13.462 --> 00:20:15.433
Hide that greasy hair,

00:20:15.433 --> 00:20:17.410
and don't let anyone notice
you skipped a shower.

00:20:17.410 --> 00:20:20.659
Good luck on your first day!

00:20:27.674 --> 00:20:30.669
Let's do this, Woo Hyun Jin.

00:20:45.909 --> 00:20:49.357
You brought everything from home?

00:20:50.409 --> 00:20:52.281
Being a contract worker can feel

00:20:52.281 --> 00:20:54.436
pretty lonely, right?

00:20:54.436 --> 00:20:55.466
Not really.

00:20:55.466 --> 00:20:57.125
I like to handle my own stuff.

00:20:57.125 --> 00:20:59.622
So, this is our department structure.

00:20:59.622 --> 00:21:01.082
Give it a quick look.

00:21:01.082 --> 00:21:02.979
I've already read it three times.

00:21:02.979 --> 00:21:06.124
Want me to read it again?

00:21:06.124 --> 00:21:08.357
Then take a look at the handover materials.

00:21:08.357 --> 00:21:09.919
I already got them from
Assistant Manager Lee Hyun Soo

00:21:09.919 --> 00:21:12.323
and printed everything out.

00:21:14.464 --> 00:21:16.864
You're an ace. Seriously.

00:21:20.985 --> 00:21:22.778
It's you, right?

00:21:22.778 --> 00:21:24.546
The lobby girl.

00:21:24.546 --> 00:21:25.690
Sorry?

00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:26.774
What do you mean...

00:21:26.774 --> 00:21:28.109
You know...

00:21:28.109 --> 00:21:30.042
The day you interviewed here,

00:21:30.042 --> 00:21:32.968
a guy yelled "Honey" on the first floor, right?

00:21:32.968 --> 00:21:34.282
An inconsiderate couple.

00:21:34.282 --> 00:21:36.916
Honey, over here.

00:21:39.716 --> 00:21:41.690
That was you, right?

00:21:42.321 --> 00:21:45.627
You're wearing the same outfit
as the girl in the video.

00:21:47.933 --> 00:21:51.179
Honey, how did the interview go?

00:21:53.470 --> 00:21:54.580
What?

00:21:54.580 --> 00:21:56.657
That was you?

00:21:56.657 --> 00:21:58.973
That clip has over a thousand views
on the internal board,

00:21:58.973 --> 00:22:00.725
and my team talks about it
every time we're at the cafeteria,

00:22:00.725 --> 00:22:03.227
wondering which team the new hire is from.

00:22:03.227 --> 00:22:04.457
But...

00:22:04.457 --> 00:22:06.407
That was you...

00:22:08.800 --> 00:22:09.873
Look again.

00:22:09.873 --> 00:22:12.819
Oh, that Pimang guy's face is crystal clear.

00:22:12.819 --> 00:22:15.605
At least you only show up from the back.

00:22:15.605 --> 00:22:17.236
Yeah?

00:22:21.122 --> 00:22:24.841
Should I just dig those dimples out?

00:22:28.225 --> 00:22:30.213
They say the boiler repair is expensive.

00:22:30.213 --> 00:22:33.299
I really don't think
I can handle bathing the baby today.

00:22:33.299 --> 00:22:35.426
That sounds pretty tough.

00:22:35.426 --> 00:22:37.056
Want to know how to fix a boiler?

00:22:37.056 --> 00:22:38.446
Yeah, let's hear it.

00:22:38.446 --> 00:22:40.877
Fixing a boiler is all about the tools.

00:22:40.877 --> 00:22:43.182
You can't even start without tools.

00:22:43.182 --> 00:22:45.188
Tools?

00:22:50.669 --> 00:22:54.153
Oh, what's wrong with you?

00:22:54.153 --> 00:22:55.571
Unit 206.

00:22:55.571 --> 00:22:56.864
You smashed all the peppers

00:22:56.864 --> 00:22:58.450
my mom had laid out to dry,

00:22:58.450 --> 00:23:00.470
then moved in making all that noise. Right?

00:23:00.470 --> 00:23:02.133
I moved in pretty quietly.

00:23:02.133 --> 00:23:04.130
Sure you did.

00:23:05.012 --> 00:23:07.333
Woo Joo.

00:23:07.333 --> 00:23:08.776
How cute.

00:23:08.776 --> 00:23:11.176
Are you playing with a toy car?

00:23:13.568 --> 00:23:15.641
Could I borrow some tools?

00:23:15.641 --> 00:23:17.469
What? Tools?

00:23:17.469 --> 00:23:18.829
What do you need them for?

00:23:18.829 --> 00:23:21.942
I need a reason before I lend them.

00:23:21.942 --> 00:23:24.643
The boiler's broken.

00:23:24.643 --> 00:23:26.929
The boiler?

00:23:26.929 --> 00:23:31.068
I can't just ignore it
when Woo Joo's boiler is broken.

00:23:31.068 --> 00:23:34.454
I actually specialize in boilers.

00:23:35.154 --> 00:23:37.153
Really?

00:23:39.891 --> 00:23:42.577
Just one look and I can tell

00:23:42.577 --> 00:23:45.079
what the problem is.

00:23:45.079 --> 00:23:48.332
It's the motor. The motor.

00:23:48.332 --> 00:23:49.876
- The motor?
- The motor.

00:23:49.876 --> 00:23:51.377
"M-o-t-o-r."

00:23:51.377 --> 00:23:52.670
I don't think that's it.

00:23:52.670 --> 00:23:54.556
Are you sure you actually know
how to fix this?

00:23:54.556 --> 00:23:58.093
Hey, my nickname's MacGyver.

00:23:58.093 --> 00:24:00.386
I've got a long education behind me.
I know this stuff.

00:24:00.386 --> 00:24:01.721
I've got connections too.

00:24:01.721 --> 00:24:05.314
The police chief is my buddy.

00:24:05.314 --> 00:24:07.554
Got it?

00:24:08.227 --> 00:24:10.354
Then why are you home?

00:24:10.354 --> 00:24:13.957
It's a weekday. Everyone's at work.

00:24:16.561 --> 00:24:17.720
Then what about you?

00:24:17.720 --> 00:24:19.163
You look perfectly fine.

00:24:19.163 --> 00:24:21.821
Why are you home at this hour?

00:24:23.466 --> 00:24:25.418
I'm...

00:24:26.454 --> 00:24:27.872
On parental leave.

00:24:27.872 --> 00:24:29.332
- Parental leave?
- Yeah.

00:24:29.332 --> 00:24:31.740
- For Woo Joo?
- Yes.

00:24:34.212 --> 00:24:36.745
Now that I think about it, who are you exactly?

00:24:36.745 --> 00:24:38.132
I know Woo Joo,

00:24:38.132 --> 00:24:40.320
but I've never seen you.

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:42.178
I've seen the lady of this house a few times,

00:24:42.178 --> 00:24:44.964
but I've never seen you.

00:24:44.964 --> 00:24:48.222
What's your relationship with her?

00:24:49.676 --> 00:24:51.103
Why can't you answer?

00:24:51.103 --> 00:24:53.242
- Hey!
- Huh?

00:24:55.909 --> 00:24:58.736
Well, you see...

00:24:58.736 --> 00:25:00.196
We're close.

00:25:00.196 --> 00:25:01.370
Close how?

00:25:01.370 --> 00:25:02.965
What do you think?

00:25:02.965 --> 00:25:05.895
We raise a "baby,"
and we call each other "babe."

00:25:05.895 --> 00:25:08.135
The baby and...

00:25:08.135 --> 00:25:10.374
The babe?

00:25:16.493 --> 00:25:18.434
First day in,

00:25:18.434 --> 00:25:22.112
and it's already chaos.

00:26:14.252 --> 00:26:15.932
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin.

00:26:15.932 --> 00:26:17.167
Where did you go?

00:26:17.167 --> 00:26:18.816
The manager is here right now.

00:26:18.816 --> 00:26:21.836
What? The manager?

00:26:42.423 --> 00:26:46.538
I have something I need to say to you today.

00:26:46.538 --> 00:26:48.365
Actually,

00:26:48.365 --> 00:26:50.336
so do I.

00:27:04.528 --> 00:27:06.593
Hello. I'm Park Yoon Seong,

00:27:06.593 --> 00:27:09.076
Manager of Planning Team 3.

00:27:12.821 --> 00:27:14.386
Only one semester left

00:27:14.386 --> 00:27:16.415
of going to school together.

00:27:16.415 --> 00:27:18.042
I know.

00:27:18.042 --> 00:27:20.068
It's a shame.

00:27:23.138 --> 00:27:25.318
Just a shame?

00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:30.587
I regret it.

00:27:30.587 --> 00:27:32.220
That I never told you

00:27:32.220 --> 00:27:34.813
how I felt sooner.

00:27:44.177 --> 00:27:46.426
Woo Hyun Jin.

00:27:46.426 --> 00:27:48.539
I...

00:27:51.636 --> 00:27:53.854
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin?

00:27:53.854 --> 00:27:56.190
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin.

00:27:57.138 --> 00:27:59.459
Yes?

00:27:59.459 --> 00:28:01.452
These are the key schedules for this quarter.

00:28:01.452 --> 00:28:02.957
Get familiar with the overall flow first,

00:28:02.957 --> 00:28:05.025
and ask if you have any questions.

00:28:05.025 --> 00:28:07.645
Yes. Thank you.

00:28:34.660 --> 00:28:36.046
Man...

00:28:36.046 --> 00:28:37.739
I don't think you should touch that.

00:28:37.739 --> 00:28:39.373
Don't tell me how to do it.

00:28:39.373 --> 00:28:41.834
Just stay still.

00:28:41.834 --> 00:28:44.177
Oh, darn it.

00:28:44.837 --> 00:28:46.797
Oh, gosh.

00:28:47.397 --> 00:28:49.510
If my in-law finds out, she's going to lose it.

00:28:49.510 --> 00:28:51.549
Hey, mister...

00:28:54.202 --> 00:28:56.942
What the hell!

00:29:08.721 --> 00:29:10.799
Sorry I'm late, Woo Joo's uncle.

00:29:10.799 --> 00:29:15.083
Since you worked overtime,
I'll take trash duty off your list.

00:29:15.083 --> 00:29:19.013
I just want to soak in hot water already.

00:29:26.462 --> 00:29:29.215
Yesterday at least the power was on.

00:29:29.215 --> 00:29:32.147
Why won't it turn on today?

00:29:32.147 --> 00:29:33.173
Hey, in-law.

00:29:33.173 --> 00:29:34.407
Did you touch anything?

00:29:34.407 --> 00:29:36.827
No. Why would I?

00:29:39.285 --> 00:29:42.671
Why isn't this working?

00:29:43.971 --> 00:29:45.231
I looked it up,

00:29:45.231 --> 00:29:47.816
stuff like this is on the landlord to fix.

00:29:47.816 --> 00:29:49.554
- Really?
- Yes, but only...

00:29:49.554 --> 00:29:51.737
if it's not the tenant's fault.

00:29:51.737 --> 00:29:54.181
We didn't do anything wrong, right?

00:29:54.181 --> 00:29:55.244
Right.

00:29:55.244 --> 00:29:57.882
I'll try calling the landlord.

00:29:59.989 --> 00:30:02.536
Did they change their number?

00:30:02.536 --> 00:30:05.118
Why aren't they picking up?

00:30:05.118 --> 00:30:06.860
This landlord's awful.

00:30:06.860 --> 00:30:10.473
They're totally ghosting us.

00:30:10.473 --> 00:30:11.749
I'll leave a text.

00:30:11.749 --> 00:30:14.220
Go ahead.

00:30:14.220 --> 00:30:16.345
The boiler's been broken for days,

00:30:16.345 --> 00:30:18.597
and it's making basic living difficult.

00:30:18.597 --> 00:30:20.641
That's way too polite.

00:30:20.641 --> 00:30:21.892
Give it to me.

00:30:21.892 --> 00:30:23.894
You need a little edge with landlords.

00:30:23.894 --> 00:30:25.437
Otherwise they'll walk all over you.

00:30:25.437 --> 00:30:26.821
I know this stuff.

00:30:26.821 --> 00:30:28.354
I've lived in a semi-basement.

00:30:28.354 --> 00:30:31.193
And with landlords,
the first line really matters.

00:30:31.193 --> 00:30:32.812
No.

00:30:32.812 --> 00:30:35.779
You need a little performance.

00:30:35.779 --> 00:30:38.645
My wife's been trying to reach you...

00:30:38.645 --> 00:30:39.702
Are you insane?

00:30:39.702 --> 00:30:42.908
Why are you making me married?

00:30:42.908 --> 00:30:46.768
What's wrong with that?

00:30:46.768 --> 00:30:49.608
My honey can't even shower because...

00:30:49.608 --> 00:30:50.838
Hey.

00:30:50.838 --> 00:30:52.364
If you don't do this,
they won't take us seriously.

00:30:52.364 --> 00:30:54.825
- It's worse when you're a woman.
- No, it's not.

00:30:54.825 --> 00:30:56.510
- Give me that.
- No. Stop.

00:30:56.510 --> 00:30:58.530
I said no.

00:31:01.409 --> 00:31:02.602
[Landlord of Yooseong Villa]

00:31:02.602 --> 00:31:04.685
Gosh, this is making me nuts.

00:31:04.685 --> 00:31:07.685
You're no help at all.

00:31:10.608 --> 00:31:13.638
Anything else I can help with?

00:31:15.390 --> 00:31:17.517
Seriously?

00:31:24.558 --> 00:31:26.530
[Landlord of Yooseong Villa]

00:31:28.204 --> 00:31:30.044
Our workload split is a mess.

00:31:30.044 --> 00:31:33.175
I keep getting dumped with overtime.

00:31:33.175 --> 00:31:34.368
Hey, in-law.

00:31:34.368 --> 00:31:36.461
Because of you, my image in life

00:31:36.461 --> 00:31:39.293
is completely wrecked.

00:31:39.293 --> 00:31:40.884
Texting the landlord like this...

00:31:40.884 --> 00:31:43.766
"Texting the landlord like this..."

00:31:43.766 --> 00:31:45.059
How was your day, guys?

00:31:45.059 --> 00:31:46.369
My team leader is such a boomer.

00:31:46.369 --> 00:31:48.652
- I want to transfer to Planning Team 3.
- Manager Park Yoon Seong?

00:31:48.652 --> 00:31:50.974
- People say he's scary but sexy.
- He looks so good in a suit.

00:31:50.974 --> 00:31:53.764
Did you guys hear?
The lobby nuisance girl got hired.

00:31:53.764 --> 00:31:57.617
- Then she's in this group chat?
- The quiet one is the culprit.

00:32:02.823 --> 00:32:05.469
Honey, over here.

00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:10.667
Honey, how did the interview go?

00:32:14.114 --> 00:32:15.792
That's me.

00:32:15.792 --> 00:32:18.111
At least you only show up from the back...

00:32:18.111 --> 00:32:21.720
Because of you,
my work life is completely screwed.

00:32:21.720 --> 00:32:23.346
What am I supposed to do now?

00:32:23.346 --> 00:32:26.132
This isn't who I am.

00:32:26.767 --> 00:32:29.306
I'm Suzy.

00:32:29.306 --> 00:32:30.437
What?

00:32:30.437 --> 00:32:32.917
To him, I'm like Suzy.

00:32:32.917 --> 00:32:34.359
I wanted to show him

00:32:34.359 --> 00:32:36.858
only the perfect version of me.

00:32:36.858 --> 00:32:38.904
Who's "him," and who's Suzy now?

00:32:38.904 --> 00:32:40.197
You don't know Suzy?

00:32:40.197 --> 00:32:41.889
Suzy from the movie "Architecture 101."

00:32:41.889 --> 00:32:44.286
I know, but...

00:32:46.929 --> 00:32:48.330
You're Suzy?

00:32:48.330 --> 00:32:49.568
Suzy?

00:32:49.568 --> 00:32:51.674
Yes, Suzy!

00:32:51.674 --> 00:32:53.127
I might be Woo Joo's aunt

00:32:53.127 --> 00:32:54.945
and your in-law, but...

00:32:54.945 --> 00:32:57.106
you know...

00:32:57.726 --> 00:33:00.488
He was my first love.

00:33:00.488 --> 00:33:02.970
Do you know how much I liked him?

00:33:02.970 --> 00:33:04.705
But not like this.

00:33:04.705 --> 00:33:07.913
I'm Suzy!

00:33:07.913 --> 00:33:09.309
Did you drink?

00:33:09.309 --> 00:33:10.714
You're kind of scaring me.

00:33:10.714 --> 00:33:13.108
I've got chills.

00:33:13.108 --> 00:33:15.109
Suzy?

00:33:17.086 --> 00:33:18.736
This doesn't feel right.

00:33:18.736 --> 00:33:19.778
The Suzys I know are

00:33:19.778 --> 00:33:22.038
Kim Suzy, Lee Suzy, Park Suzy,
Choi Suzy, and then there's Bae Suzy.

00:33:22.038 --> 00:33:24.283
You're saying you mean that Bae Suzy.

00:33:24.283 --> 00:33:27.064
Yes! That Bae Suzy!

00:33:29.121 --> 00:33:30.247
I am Suzy.

00:33:30.247 --> 00:33:31.540
This joke is going too far.

00:33:31.540 --> 00:33:33.500
The funny one is Lee Suzy.

00:33:33.500 --> 00:33:36.166
I really am Suzy to him...

00:33:38.509 --> 00:33:41.256
[Boiler Broken, Day 3]

00:33:42.676 --> 00:33:43.802
It's cold.

00:33:43.802 --> 00:33:45.605
Woo Joo, here.

00:33:45.605 --> 00:33:48.038
You're eating well.

00:33:53.896 --> 00:33:56.565
You heated water to wash up? This early?

00:33:56.565 --> 00:33:58.484
No. I didn't have time.

00:33:58.484 --> 00:34:01.356
I just took a cold shower.

00:34:01.356 --> 00:34:02.757
You'll catch a cold.

00:34:02.757 --> 00:34:05.697
My work life matters more right now.

00:34:06.646 --> 00:34:09.313
Make sure he finishes all his food,

00:34:09.313 --> 00:34:12.157
and send me a proof shot.

00:34:24.025 --> 00:34:26.292
- Want to eat?
- Yeah.

00:34:35.675 --> 00:34:37.788
You're eating so well.

00:34:47.692 --> 00:34:49.519
[Interview Hacks]

00:34:53.633 --> 00:34:55.658
[Job Interview Tips]

00:35:21.068 --> 00:35:23.093
[Boiler Broken]

00:35:23.093 --> 00:35:25.148
[Day 4]

00:35:29.216 --> 00:35:31.975
Did you shower with cold water again?

00:35:48.244 --> 00:35:49.365
Ms. Hyun Jin, hello.

00:35:49.365 --> 00:35:50.517
Good morning.

00:35:50.517 --> 00:35:51.916
Hi.

00:35:51.916 --> 00:35:54.114
The Manager's on a business trip
until tomorrow.

00:35:54.114 --> 00:35:55.475
Oh, really?

00:35:55.475 --> 00:35:56.476
Thank goodness.

00:35:56.476 --> 00:35:58.109
He's always working so hard.

00:35:58.109 --> 00:35:59.479
If he's not in tomorrow,

00:35:59.479 --> 00:36:02.412
I can probably skip a shower for one more day.

00:36:04.254 --> 00:36:05.286
[Boiler Broken]

00:36:05.286 --> 00:36:07.684
[Day 5]
His trip goes through today, right?

00:36:07.684 --> 00:36:10.212
You sure you're okay?

00:36:10.212 --> 00:36:11.697
You look kind of pale.

00:36:11.697 --> 00:36:13.870
I didn't wash my hair with cold water today.

00:36:13.870 --> 00:36:15.576
I'm fine.

00:36:15.576 --> 00:36:18.268
Woo Joo, see you later.

00:36:24.337 --> 00:36:25.989
Does your aunt look grimy?

00:36:25.989 --> 00:36:27.931
Yeah.

00:36:39.478 --> 00:36:42.648
Gosh, I didn't even shower.

00:36:42.648 --> 00:36:44.462
They said he was on a trip through today.

00:36:44.462 --> 00:36:46.635
Why is he here?

00:36:53.659 --> 00:36:56.479
What did you get all over this?

00:36:59.698 --> 00:37:04.086
One broken boiler and
parenting just got way harder.

00:37:04.086 --> 00:37:05.811
- Hey, kid.
- Yeah.

00:37:05.811 --> 00:37:08.539
You need another bath today, right?

00:37:11.760 --> 00:37:14.446
I need to shower too.

00:37:17.734 --> 00:37:21.087
She's really getting to me.

00:37:21.812 --> 00:37:23.792
Whatever.

00:37:38.887 --> 00:37:41.739
I'll pay you a million won for the day.

00:37:49.991 --> 00:37:51.142
Now?

00:37:51.142 --> 00:37:52.742
We're supposed to watch him?

00:37:52.742 --> 00:37:55.015
What? Why?

00:37:55.015 --> 00:37:56.435
Does this make any sense?

00:37:56.435 --> 00:37:57.828
I don't know.

00:37:57.828 --> 00:37:59.266
Sun Tae Hyung, where did you...

00:37:59.266 --> 00:38:00.994
Where did he go, Woo Joo?

00:38:00.994 --> 00:38:03.757
- Woo Joo.
- Peekaboo.

00:38:17.190 --> 00:38:19.643
I knew you'd show up.

00:38:20.560 --> 00:38:22.589
That one million you mentioned before,

00:38:22.589 --> 00:38:23.989
it's getting transferred today, right?

00:38:23.989 --> 00:38:25.124
Of course.

00:38:25.124 --> 00:38:27.857
As soon as we're done.

00:38:27.857 --> 00:38:30.054
It's the first time in ten years

00:38:30.054 --> 00:38:31.840
a place was chosen this fast.

00:38:31.840 --> 00:38:34.090
It's all thanks to you.

00:38:35.185 --> 00:38:37.685
Now today,

00:38:37.685 --> 00:38:39.685
there's just one thing you need to remember.

00:38:39.685 --> 00:38:40.721
What is it?

00:38:40.721 --> 00:38:42.268
Never...

00:38:42.268 --> 00:38:44.455
Show off.

00:38:44.455 --> 00:38:46.175
Just because you've done this work before,

00:38:46.175 --> 00:38:47.376
don't touch anything.

00:38:47.376 --> 00:38:49.016
Amy Choo hates that the most.

00:38:49.016 --> 00:38:50.333
No opinions. No ego.

00:38:50.333 --> 00:38:52.152
Just say "yes, yes, got it."

00:38:52.152 --> 00:38:53.565
Got it?

00:38:53.565 --> 00:38:55.456
Yes, yes, got it.

00:38:55.456 --> 00:38:56.592
Okay.

00:38:56.592 --> 00:38:58.672
Just get through it without messing up.

00:38:58.672 --> 00:38:59.872
Please.

00:38:59.872 --> 00:39:01.536
I'm begging you.

00:39:01.536 --> 00:39:03.468
I'm going in.

00:39:06.740 --> 00:39:08.311
- Let's skip this one entirely.
- Okay.

00:39:08.311 --> 00:39:10.891
Could you look at the camera, please?

00:39:14.716 --> 00:39:16.196
Let's get some light on the face.

00:39:16.196 --> 00:39:18.678
Please move the reflector slightly to the left.

00:39:18.678 --> 00:39:20.013
Is this position okay?

00:39:20.013 --> 00:39:22.340
Yes, one moment.

00:39:32.359 --> 00:39:34.899
Turn your head slightly to the left.

00:39:34.899 --> 00:39:36.471
Should we adjust the key light a bit?

00:39:36.471 --> 00:39:37.519
Sorry?

00:39:37.519 --> 00:39:39.632
Oh yes, yes.

00:39:41.442 --> 00:39:43.934
A little more to the right.

00:39:54.923 --> 00:39:56.842
Hello, guys.

00:39:56.842 --> 00:39:59.489
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:39:59.489 --> 00:40:00.799
How's the lighting setup?

00:40:00.799 --> 00:40:01.930
All set.

00:40:01.930 --> 00:40:04.865
Key light is locked in.

00:40:04.865 --> 00:40:06.691
Who are you?

00:40:06.691 --> 00:40:08.810
Just a day hire.

00:40:08.810 --> 00:40:10.377
I don't use assistants. Leave.

00:40:10.377 --> 00:40:11.476
No.

00:40:11.476 --> 00:40:13.882
I need to make that million.

00:40:15.459 --> 00:40:18.216
- Hey...
- I can't do this!

00:40:18.216 --> 00:40:20.816
I'm not shooting!

00:40:20.816 --> 00:40:22.909
Are you trying to screw me over?

00:40:22.909 --> 00:40:25.121
Or push me even further down?

00:40:25.121 --> 00:40:26.830
I already got branded as the affair girl,

00:40:26.830 --> 00:40:28.795
lost every ad deal I had.

00:40:28.795 --> 00:40:30.906
Are you insane?

00:40:30.906 --> 00:40:32.182
I can't do this.

00:40:32.182 --> 00:40:34.635
Change the shoot concept!

00:40:35.735 --> 00:40:38.045
Then get out.

00:40:38.045 --> 00:40:41.708
I don't work with people
who don't trust my camera.

00:40:47.213 --> 00:40:50.770
I don't care if you had an affair or not.

00:40:50.770 --> 00:40:54.434
I don't care what's real or fake
in your private life.

00:40:54.434 --> 00:40:55.847
But when you came to me,

00:40:55.847 --> 00:40:59.656
you were asking me
to show who you are right now.

00:40:59.656 --> 00:41:01.683
You don't have to trust me.

00:41:01.683 --> 00:41:04.830
But you do have to trust my camera.

00:41:04.830 --> 00:41:06.222
From this moment on,

00:41:06.222 --> 00:41:09.207
I'm using my camera to change

00:41:09.207 --> 00:41:12.127
how people see you.

00:41:12.127 --> 00:41:14.033
So, what now?

00:41:14.669 --> 00:41:17.148
The choice is yours.

00:41:22.969 --> 00:41:24.888
Chin, just a little.

00:41:24.888 --> 00:41:26.531
Camera.

00:41:29.226 --> 00:41:31.061
Good.

00:41:52.645 --> 00:41:53.856
What are you doing?

00:41:53.856 --> 00:41:56.515
After five, the natural light drops off.

00:41:56.515 --> 00:41:59.635
But then the neon signs spill inward instead.

00:41:59.635 --> 00:42:01.758
It gives the subject a strong back tone,

00:42:01.758 --> 00:42:05.191
which works really well for evening shots.

00:42:05.191 --> 00:42:09.535
You are going for high contrast, right?

00:42:09.535 --> 00:42:10.782
Like...

00:42:10.782 --> 00:42:14.289
the 2018 Tesser cover shoot.

00:42:15.407 --> 00:42:16.683
So...

00:42:16.683 --> 00:42:19.943
you adjusted things without my direction?

00:42:21.287 --> 00:42:23.322
I know you hate it...

00:42:23.322 --> 00:42:25.569
- when people overstep on set.
- And?

00:42:25.569 --> 00:42:28.060
I'm just a one-day temp.

00:42:28.778 --> 00:42:31.698
So I do not have to play it safe.

00:42:31.698 --> 00:42:35.394
I will just pull the edge and drop the key.

00:42:35.394 --> 00:42:38.817
You like it a little rough in color anyway.

00:42:39.629 --> 00:42:41.494
So...

00:42:41.494 --> 00:42:43.987
Can I keep going?

00:42:47.095 --> 00:42:49.695
The launch date for our new product
has been finalized.

00:42:49.695 --> 00:42:53.052
As you all know, the domestic HMR market
is already saturated.

00:42:53.052 --> 00:42:55.813
Without clear differentiation,
it will be hard to gain market share.

00:42:55.813 --> 00:42:58.574
So we need detailed strategies
by distribution channel...

00:42:58.574 --> 00:42:59.655
Oh.

00:42:59.655 --> 00:43:01.427
Manager, does that mean

00:43:01.427 --> 00:43:04.154
we are reconsidering overseas expansion?

00:43:04.154 --> 00:43:05.674
Yes.

00:43:05.674 --> 00:43:07.627
Since this is our first launch,

00:43:07.627 --> 00:43:10.410
I think we should focus on
building brand awareness.

00:43:10.410 --> 00:43:11.453
Right.

00:43:11.453 --> 00:43:13.954
Securing a strong domestic response
does come first...

00:43:13.954 --> 00:43:15.621
But still,

00:43:15.621 --> 00:43:17.694
is this not an opportunity?

00:43:17.694 --> 00:43:19.669
Based on the materials you put together,

00:43:19.669 --> 00:43:21.455
the timing looks right.

00:43:21.455 --> 00:43:25.575
We should not miss this opportunity this time.

00:43:29.152 --> 00:43:31.972
Thank you.

00:43:48.519 --> 00:43:50.439
Amy Choo?

00:43:50.439 --> 00:43:52.464
You really worked as her assistant?

00:43:52.464 --> 00:43:55.045
- So you're her first assistant ever.
- Don't get carried away.

00:43:55.045 --> 00:43:56.465
It was just a one-day gig.

00:43:56.465 --> 00:43:58.666
She used to be your role model, right?

00:43:58.666 --> 00:44:01.022
How does this happen right after you quit?

00:44:01.022 --> 00:44:03.421
Well, I tried it once. That is enough for me.

00:44:03.421 --> 00:44:05.127
You said you were done with photography.

00:44:05.127 --> 00:44:07.361
But you still went to the shoot. Why?

00:44:07.361 --> 00:44:08.652
Nothing.

00:44:08.652 --> 00:44:11.151
Just a one-night dream.

00:44:11.151 --> 00:44:12.414
You know me.

00:44:12.414 --> 00:44:14.415
I choose reality over dreams.

00:44:14.415 --> 00:44:15.655
Either way,

00:44:15.655 --> 00:44:18.261
mission accomplished.

00:44:18.261 --> 00:44:20.605
Starting tomorrow, we finally get hot water.

00:44:20.605 --> 00:44:23.051
Hot water?

00:44:23.051 --> 00:44:25.193
There are things I can't fully explain.

00:44:25.193 --> 00:44:26.686
That is what parenting is like.

00:44:26.686 --> 00:44:29.276
It is always full of variables.

00:44:29.276 --> 00:44:31.578
Come on, kid. Let's go.

00:44:48.074 --> 00:44:50.153
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin.

00:44:51.628 --> 00:44:53.781
Let's call it a day.

00:44:54.864 --> 00:44:56.914
Yes.

00:45:06.296 --> 00:45:08.249
Floor 1.

00:45:15.847 --> 00:45:18.149
Cancel Floor 1.

00:45:20.282 --> 00:45:22.408
I'll give you a ride.

00:45:29.214 --> 00:45:31.655
- Here is one million won in cash.
- Yeah.

00:45:31.655 --> 00:45:33.551
You should have hot water from now on.

00:45:33.551 --> 00:45:35.937
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

00:45:37.010 --> 00:45:38.286
Thank you. Bye.

00:45:38.286 --> 00:45:40.201
Bye.

00:45:48.964 --> 00:45:50.983
Why does housework pile up like this

00:45:50.983 --> 00:45:54.571
just from taking one day off?

00:45:59.683 --> 00:46:01.525
Wait...

00:46:04.113 --> 00:46:06.146
Hey, kid.

00:46:07.911 --> 00:46:09.925
Hey.

00:46:11.372 --> 00:46:13.652
All of this?

00:46:23.677 --> 00:46:26.382
I'm not waiting for you anymore.

00:46:26.382 --> 00:46:28.452
This time,

00:46:28.452 --> 00:46:30.839
I'm the one leaving you behind.

00:47:01.285 --> 00:47:03.915
When did you move here?

00:47:05.064 --> 00:47:07.181
Well...

00:47:08.774 --> 00:47:11.907
It's been a while.

00:47:11.907 --> 00:47:13.942
When was it?

00:47:15.773 --> 00:47:18.907
It's really been a long time, hasn't it?

00:47:20.888 --> 00:47:22.979
About seven years?

00:47:22.979 --> 00:47:25.439
Since we went our separate ways...

00:47:31.395 --> 00:47:33.482
Yeah.

00:47:34.242 --> 00:47:37.577
We haven't seen each other once since then.

00:47:37.577 --> 00:47:38.952
I never thought

00:47:38.952 --> 00:47:42.012
I'd run into you like this.

00:47:43.119 --> 00:47:45.121
Yeah.

00:47:45.121 --> 00:47:48.793
I didn't expect to see you again on my team.

00:47:50.032 --> 00:47:52.492
I thought you'd completely forgotten about me.

00:47:52.492 --> 00:47:54.530
You never even acknowledged me at work.

00:47:54.530 --> 00:47:57.497
So that bothered you?

00:48:01.857 --> 00:48:03.367
No.

00:48:03.367 --> 00:48:05.392
That's not what I mean.

00:48:05.392 --> 00:48:07.283
Anyway...

00:48:07.949 --> 00:48:10.652
Let's do well from here on out.

00:48:23.742 --> 00:48:25.662
I lied to him again.

00:48:25.662 --> 00:48:28.024
Back then or now,

00:48:28.024 --> 00:48:30.564
you're always the same, Woo Hyun Jin.

00:48:42.760 --> 00:48:44.626
Woo Hyun Jin.

00:48:44.626 --> 00:48:46.484
I...

00:48:52.370 --> 00:48:53.607
You can take that.

00:48:53.607 --> 00:48:56.313
Bad timing...

00:48:57.992 --> 00:49:00.498
Just a second.

00:49:16.384 --> 00:49:18.384
Yoon Seong.

00:49:19.090 --> 00:49:22.436
I told you earlier I had something to say.

00:49:23.534 --> 00:49:25.741
Actually...

00:49:27.933 --> 00:49:30.579
I'm leaving soon for a language program.

00:49:33.229 --> 00:49:35.239
So...

00:49:38.155 --> 00:49:41.335
I don't think we can see each other anymore.

00:50:11.478 --> 00:50:14.804
Leave it. I'll clean it up later.

00:50:17.744 --> 00:50:20.242
Did you get caught in the rain?

00:50:20.859 --> 00:50:22.623
Didn't you have an umbrella?

00:50:22.623 --> 00:50:24.334
What happened to you?

00:50:24.334 --> 00:50:26.169
What's going on with this place?

00:50:26.169 --> 00:50:28.315
Well...

00:50:29.078 --> 00:50:32.010
I had stuff going on today too.

00:50:32.010 --> 00:50:34.082
I had an appointment.

00:50:34.082 --> 00:50:35.309
An appointment?

00:50:35.309 --> 00:50:37.793
So you went out today?

00:50:37.793 --> 00:50:38.949
Then what about Woo Joo?

00:50:38.949 --> 00:50:41.838
I left the baby somewhere safe,
just for a bit...

00:50:41.838 --> 00:50:43.953
Hey, in-law.

00:50:43.953 --> 00:50:46.003
Isn't this against what we agreed on?

00:50:46.003 --> 00:50:47.344
Agreed on what?

00:50:47.344 --> 00:50:48.526
Yes.

00:50:48.526 --> 00:50:50.752
You said you'd keep the place clean.

00:50:50.752 --> 00:50:52.638
That was the deal.

00:50:52.638 --> 00:50:54.185
And if you take him out like today,

00:50:54.185 --> 00:50:56.728
- you're supposed to tell me.
- Tell you?

00:50:56.728 --> 00:50:59.943
Do you even know why I went out today?

00:51:02.670 --> 00:51:05.838
I did something I never do,
because of this place.

00:51:05.838 --> 00:51:09.173
I picked up a camera
for the first time in three years.

00:51:09.173 --> 00:51:10.246
A camera?

00:51:10.246 --> 00:51:11.910
Okay, listen.

00:51:11.910 --> 00:51:13.328
When I moved in here,

00:51:13.328 --> 00:51:16.110
I set one condition, right?

00:51:16.110 --> 00:51:18.515
That no one goes into my space.

00:51:18.515 --> 00:51:22.342
But today the kid went into my room
and my camera...

00:51:23.361 --> 00:51:25.361
No.

00:51:25.361 --> 00:51:27.676
Let's stop.

00:51:27.676 --> 00:51:29.256
Ever since I started living with you,

00:51:29.256 --> 00:51:31.050
everything keeps going wrong.

00:51:31.050 --> 00:51:33.867
Because of me?

00:51:33.867 --> 00:51:35.943
I'm the one who's getting labeled at work

00:51:35.943 --> 00:51:37.129
because of you.

00:51:37.129 --> 00:51:39.282
I've been sick for days,
and today I didn't even get to shower.

00:51:39.282 --> 00:51:40.362
So...

00:51:40.362 --> 00:51:43.044
That's why I took a side job.

00:51:43.044 --> 00:51:45.487
The baby looks like a mess.
The place looks like a mess.

00:51:45.487 --> 00:51:48.073
- And you look like a mess too.
- Mess?

00:51:48.073 --> 00:51:49.627
Did you just call me a mess?

00:51:49.627 --> 00:51:52.460
You really just said that to me...

00:51:55.370 --> 00:51:57.301
Yes, you're right.

00:51:57.301 --> 00:52:00.977
I look terrible, don't I?

00:52:00.977 --> 00:52:03.766
I know I'm a mess.

00:52:03.766 --> 00:52:06.048
Hey, that's not...

00:52:06.048 --> 00:52:07.175
what I meant.

00:52:07.175 --> 00:52:09.093
I didn't even get to shower,

00:52:09.093 --> 00:52:11.214
so I looked like a total mess
in front of him today.

00:52:11.214 --> 00:52:13.773
I know I looked awful.

00:52:13.773 --> 00:52:14.849
"Him?"

00:52:14.849 --> 00:52:16.980
And I got completely soaked in the rain.

00:52:16.980 --> 00:52:18.353
So go inside and shower.

00:52:18.353 --> 00:52:19.639
The water's freezing.

00:52:19.639 --> 00:52:21.657
Cold showers are brutal, you know.

00:52:21.657 --> 00:52:23.059
It's fixed.

00:52:23.059 --> 00:52:26.485
I called a repair guy today. You can wash.

00:52:27.339 --> 00:52:29.465
Really?

00:52:56.659 --> 00:52:58.212
Why are you drinking beer

00:52:58.212 --> 00:53:00.619
without any food?

00:53:03.582 --> 00:53:05.542
Want one?

00:53:10.045 --> 00:53:14.085
Honestly, I'm in the mood for soju today,

00:53:14.085 --> 00:53:16.579
but we didn't have any.

00:53:20.707 --> 00:53:23.420
Hold on.

00:53:30.359 --> 00:53:32.152
No soju, but instead,

00:53:32.152 --> 00:53:36.169
Chteau de Lyon Elegance Sauvignon...

00:53:36.169 --> 00:53:38.978
It's the budget version.

00:53:39.841 --> 00:53:42.644
Wine just feels right

00:53:42.644 --> 00:53:45.077
on a rainy day.

00:53:45.077 --> 00:53:47.830
Wait, we don't have wine glasses?

00:53:49.085 --> 00:53:51.398
Thanks.

00:54:02.826 --> 00:54:04.380
Actually,

00:54:04.380 --> 00:54:07.293
I kind of wanted a drink today too.

00:54:11.878 --> 00:54:14.281
You know what?

00:54:14.281 --> 00:54:18.021
I usually love rainy days.

00:54:20.307 --> 00:54:23.542
Why do you like rainy days?

00:54:23.542 --> 00:54:25.979
Your shoes get soaked.

00:54:25.979 --> 00:54:28.440
Your clothes get soaked.

00:54:28.440 --> 00:54:31.432
It just puts you in a bad mood.

00:54:31.432 --> 00:54:32.934
Exactly.

00:54:32.934 --> 00:54:35.725
I was in a bad mood today too.

00:54:35.725 --> 00:54:38.338
I got completely soaked, and...

00:54:39.431 --> 00:54:42.125
maybe it's because I lied.

00:54:42.960 --> 00:54:44.230
But

00:54:44.230 --> 00:54:46.215
thanks to the boiler you fixed,

00:54:46.215 --> 00:54:48.763
I took a warm bath,

00:54:48.763 --> 00:54:51.254
and it helped calm me down.

00:54:53.840 --> 00:54:56.552
But where did you get the money?

00:54:56.552 --> 00:54:58.930
You said you didn't have any.

00:54:58.930 --> 00:55:00.743
Hey, in-law.

00:55:00.743 --> 00:55:02.174
I do own a house, you know.

00:55:02.174 --> 00:55:03.553
And today,

00:55:03.553 --> 00:55:04.976
I...

00:55:04.976 --> 00:55:07.832
I fixed it with what I made
from a one-day part-time job.

00:55:09.147 --> 00:55:11.672
But still...

00:55:11.672 --> 00:55:14.727
I don't really have money right now.

00:55:15.807 --> 00:55:19.073
Can I pay you back
in five monthly installments?

00:55:20.116 --> 00:55:21.589
Fine.

00:55:21.589 --> 00:55:23.878
I'll be moving out soon anyway.

00:55:23.878 --> 00:55:25.484
Do you want to keep seeing me

00:55:25.484 --> 00:55:27.465
for five more months?

00:55:27.465 --> 00:55:30.436
Let's just live like this for now

00:55:30.436 --> 00:55:32.981
and not get any more involved.

00:55:32.981 --> 00:55:35.780
That's what I want.

00:55:35.780 --> 00:55:36.878
Living with you,

00:55:36.878 --> 00:55:38.644
everything keeps going wrong for me too.

00:55:38.644 --> 00:55:39.887
I want it to stop.

00:55:39.887 --> 00:55:41.754
I feel the same way.

00:55:41.754 --> 00:55:44.232
Things get even more messed up because of you.

00:55:44.232 --> 00:55:46.269
Let's stop getting involved.

00:55:46.269 --> 00:55:49.219
Let's keep clear boundaries.

00:55:49.219 --> 00:55:52.392
Let's get through
the rest of the time peacefully.

00:56:36.394 --> 00:56:38.986
My head...

00:57:01.230 --> 00:57:04.074
Too bright...

00:57:09.143 --> 00:57:11.705
Why are you here?

00:57:11.705 --> 00:57:15.118
Why are you sleeping in my arms?

00:58:19.970 --> 00:58:21.700
What? You slept with him?

00:58:21.700 --> 00:58:25.046
What did you do to me?

00:58:26.059 --> 00:58:27.110
Wait,

00:58:27.110 --> 00:58:30.387
does he look like a man to you
now that you slept with him?

00:58:30.387 --> 00:58:32.284
Do you think she's beautiful?

00:58:32.284 --> 00:58:34.028
Are you really okay with this?

00:58:34.028 --> 00:58:35.428
What's wrong with you?

00:58:35.428 --> 00:58:37.441
How about writing the initial proposal?

00:58:37.441 --> 00:58:38.498
Yeah, sir.

00:58:38.498 --> 00:58:40.258
Just until this project is over.

00:58:40.258 --> 00:58:42.419
Please take care of Woo Joo a little longer.

00:58:42.419 --> 00:58:44.565
Why did that manager walk you home?

00:58:44.565 --> 00:58:46.175
I wanted to spend the night with you.

00:58:46.175 --> 00:58:48.777
It was driving me crazy the whole time.